lead_paragraph: CHUNGKING, China, July 2 (U.P.) -- Today's war communique said the Chinese had "successfully checked" Japanese attacks to close the thirty-five-mile gap between their eastbound and westbound spearheads at Iyang and Shangjao, on the Kiangsi part of the Hangchow-Nanchang railway.
abstract: Chinese check Jap advance, Wuyuan, Suiyan
